<Markdown>
  ### `artDirectives`

  **Type:** `ArtDirective[]`

  *An `ArtDirective` object can take all the props supported by the `<Picture />` component except `alt`, `preload`, `loading`, `decoding`, `layout`, and `fadeInTransition`. The only addition is `media`. Only the [`src`](#src) and [`media`](#media) properties are required.*

  **Default:** `undefined`

  The list of art directions to be applied to the generated picture.

  **Code Example:**
</Markdown>

<CodeExample
  {...Astro.props}
  values={[
    {
      src: "/src/images/landscape.jpg",
      alt: "alt text",
      artDirectives: `[
    {
      media: "(max-aspect-ratio: 3/2)",
      src: "/src/images/portrait.jpg",
      breakpoints: [256, 384, 576],
      width: 768,
      height: 1024,
      format: ["avif"],
      fallbackFormat: "webp",
      includeSourceFormat: false,
    },
  ]`,
    },
  ]}
/>

